genresAdvancedInfo.name: mexican traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Mexican traditional music is a genre that encompasses a range of styles, from mariachi to ranchera, son jarocho to huapango. It is characterized by its use of traditional instruments such as the guitar, accordion, and trumpet, and its lyrics often tell stories of love, loss, and Mexican culture. The music is lively and upbeat, and is often played at celebrations such as weddings and quinceañeras.
